{#- LLM-facing text is English-only: Cyrillic uses roughly 2–3× more tokens per word.
    This Jinja comment is stripped and never sent to the model.
    docs/ARCHITECTURE.md §6.2: tool-spec for route `memory_query`. -#}
{
  "type": "function",
  "function": {
    "name": "memory_query",
    "description": "Retrieve from the agent's unified knowledge base and memory (LightRAG): indexed domain knowledge (ontology, documentation, rules, facts) AND previously recorded thread_memory / global_memory notes and past conversations. This is the targeted knowledge-access mechanism — use it to look up a specific fact, recall something recorded earlier, or check reference material when the current context blocks (<knowledge_graph>, <thread_memory>, <global_memory>) do not already contain it. Returns a focused answer without rebuilding the full context.\n\nWhen NOT to use: do not query for something already present in <knowledge_graph>/<thread_memory>/<global_memory> — answer directly. Do not use for a broad multi-entity cross-reference or full context rebuild — that is reflect. Do not use to fetch external/world state — that needs cli_intent.\n\nFailure mode: vague queries retrieve poorly. Prefer a precise, entity-specific question (e.g. 'What is the retention policy for archived threads?') over a broad one (e.g. 'tell me about retention').",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "query": {
          "type": "string",
          "minLength": 1,
          "maxLength": 4000,
          "description": "Specific question to retrieve from the knowledge base / memory. Be precise — the query is passed directly to the RAG retrieval engine over the unified knowledge+memory graph."
        },
        "reasoning": {
          "type": "string",
          "minLength": 1,
          "maxLength": 2000,
          "description": "Why this knowledge lookup is needed — short text for logs."
        }
      },
      "required": ["query", "reasoning"],
      "additionalProperties": false
    }
  }
}
